Steps:

1.	Type ./build.sh to rebuild the project whenever you move the project to
	a new environment, or you edit the source files.
	
	The configuration files of cmake, as well as the generated Makefile will 
	be placed in the folder build.
	
	The executable file will be placed in the folder build/bin. 

2.	Type ./run.sh to run the executable file.
	
